# Locale.Region

**Structure**

A type that represents a geographic region, for use in specifying a locale or language.

## Declaration

```swift
struct Region
```

## Creating a region

- **init(_:)**: Creates a region from a BCP 47 identifier.

## Examining region properties

- **identifier**: The BCP 47 identifier of the region.
- **containingRegion**: The region that contains this region, if any.
- **continent**: The continent that contains this region, if any.
- **isISORegion**: A Boolean value that indicates whether the region is an ISO-defined region.
- **subRegions**: An array of all the sub-regions of the region.

## Using special-purpose regions

- **unknown**: A pre-defined unknown or invalid region.

## Getting a list of regions

- **isoRegions**: An array of regions defined by ISO.

## Structures

- **Locale.Region.Category**: Categories of a region. See https://www.unicode.org/reports/tr35/tr35-35/tr35-info.html#Territory_Data

## Instance Properties

- **category**: The category of the region.
- **subcontinent**: The subcontinent that contains this region, if any.

## Instance Methods

- **subRegions(ofCategory:)**: An array of the sub-regions, matching the specified category of the region.

## Type Methods

- **isoRegions(ofCategory:)**: An array of regions matching the specified categories.

## Getting region components

- **region**: The region used by the locale.
- **subdivision**: The optional subdivision of the region used by this locale.
- **Locale.Subdivision**: A type that represents a subdivision of a region, such as a state in the US or a province in Canada.
- **variant**: An optional variant used by the locale.
- **Locale.Variant**: A type that represents a locale’s languate variant.
